CANON INFORMATION
From Official Spoiler Document:

"Not shy, just introverted"

Key Distinction:

Not Shy: Doesn't have social anxiety or fear of interaction
Just Introverted: Prefers solitude, recharges energy by being alone, chooses quiet over loud

From Mayamail (Semi-Canon):

Doesn't initiate greetings (stood in silence during Maya hallway encounter)
Talks very little ("talks at least as little as I do" per Maya)
Stays overnight at friends' houses (comfortable with band for sleepovers)
Participates in long conversations when comfortable (five-hour late-night band conversation)

From Studio Massa (Canon):

The book she's reading during the series is a romance novel


PHYSICAL APPEARANCE
Hair: Dark brown, shoulder-length, slightly messy
Eyes: Dark brown
Build: Short/petite - shortest member of the band (approximately 5'2")
Skin: Fair/light complexion
Notable Accessory: Always wears a scarf (acts as comfort item and personal "armor")
Clothing Style:

Pink/purple striped shirt (casual, comfortable)
Practical, cozy clothing
Dresses for comfort over fashion

Presence: Very easy to miss in crowd scenes; naturally fades into background

INTERESTS & ACTIVITIES
Reading - Romance Novels (Canon):
Massa confirmed she reads romance books during the series. This reveals:

Quiet girl surrounded by death (funeral home) escapes into stories about love and connection
Contrast between her solemn daily reality and romantic fantasy
Like Maya's anime escapism but healthier - still engaging with human emotion/relationships
Possibly reads romance because she's too introverted to pursue it herself
Lives vicariously through fictional relationships

Likely Reading List:

Contemporary romance
Maybe historical romance (fits her thoughtful nature)
Character-driven love stories
Probably prefers slow-burn romances over explicit content
Spanish romance authors if bilingual (María Dueñas, etc.)

What This Means:

She's a romantic despite her reserved exterior
Understands love/connection intellectually even if she struggles with it practically
The funeral home girl reading about life and love = poetic irony
Quiet observer who understands human emotion deeply

Music - "Running in the 60's" Band:

Role: Bass guitarist
Genre: Eurobeat folk
Band Members: Cleo (vocals/guitar), Coco (drums), Yfke (synthesizer), Zoey (bass)


FAMILY BACKGROUND
Funeral Home Heritage:
Born into family running generational funeral home business. Raised surrounded by silence, solemnity, and death from young age. Parents taught her to approach life and death with respect and calm professionalism.
Impact on Character:

Comfort with silence stems from funeral home atmosphere
Respectful, measured approach to interactions
Not disturbed by dark or morbid topics
Understanding of grief, loss, and human fragility
Mature beyond her years
Reads romance as escape from constant death - needs stories about life, love, beginnings instead of endings

Spanish Heritage:
Family immigrated from Spain to Netherlands. Funeral home might incorporate Spanish death rituals/customs. Bilingual (Spanish at home, Dutch at school). Reads Spanish literature and romance novels in original language.
Why This Matters:

Spanish culture has rich relationship with death (Día de los Muertos influence)
Catholic funeral traditions = respect for ritual and ceremony
Another cultural outsider like other Ongezellig characters
Spanish romance novels = connection to heritage


THE ROMANCE BOOK SIGNIFICANCE
The Mortician's Daughter Reading Romance:
Someone who deals with death daily escaping into stories about love and life. The quiet girl who watches relationships form around her (Cleo's band friendships, Coco's popularity) but doesn't participate - instead she reads about fictional ones.
Contrast to Maya:

Maya: Escapes into anime/hentai (sexual fantasy, completely removed from reality)
Zoey: Escapes into romance (emotional connection, still grounded in human relationships)
Maya's escapism is isolating, Zoey's is aspirational
Both are introverts who struggle with connection, but Zoey's outlet is healthier

Why She Doesn't Pursue Romance Herself:

Too introverted to initiate
Comfortable observing rather than participating
Funeral home background = understands everything ends, maybe hesitant to begin
Has friends (band) so emotional needs partially met
Content with vicarious experience through books

Band Might Not Know:

Probably hides romance novel covers (embarrassed?)
Friends think she reads "literature"
Actually reading bodice-rippers and slow-burn love stories
This would be her secret - the quiet girl has romantic side


