THEMATIC SIGNIFICANCE
The Healthy Introvert vs. Maya:
Both are extremely quiet and struggle with initiating conversation, but:

Zoey: Accepted herself → has friends, reads romance, participates in band
Maya: Hates herself → isolated, watches hentai, only imaginary friends

Zoey represents what Maya could have been - an introvert who found compatible friend group and healthy escapism (romance novels about human connection vs. hentai about sexual fantasy).
Death and Romance:
Funeral home girl reading romance novels = someone surrounded by endings who craves stories about beginnings. She understands mortality deeply, which might make love seem both precious and frightening. She observes rather than participates - safer to read about it.
Cultural Integration:
Spanish girl in Dutch school who found acceptance through music. Maintains heritage (Spanish language, possibly Spanish funeral customs) while integrating successfully. Contrast to Mymy (rejects Japanese heritage) and Maya (can't integrate at all).

